{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17503663","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17503663"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:05:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:05:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2062"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2062","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2062"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.02,0.03,0.38,0.46]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2062"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111539"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2062","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2062"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2062"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93626"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"98"},{"type":"tags","id":"191"},{"type":"tags","id":"1453"},{"type":"tags","id":"3505"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"10"},{"type":"contributions","id":"282"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39167"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42445"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44524"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111539","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/111539"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 35-year-old man is being counselled with regards to possible bariatric surgery. Despite trying various dietary modifications, he has been unable to reduce his BMI to less than 35 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E. When he initially sought help, his BMI was 42 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E. He has a medical history of type 2 diabetes, hypertension and hyperlipidaemia. His medications include metformin. He is determined to improve his overall health and the bariatric surgeon has advised that a Roux-en-Y gastric bypass would be appropriate. The short and long-term consequences of the procedure are discussed.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following expectations would be most applicable as a consequence of surgery?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Considerable risk in regaining the initial loss in weight","Reduction in risk of prostate cancer","Increased risk of severe depression","Increased risk of biliary disease","Increased risk of gastro-oesophageal reflux disease"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ERoux-en-Y gastric bypass is probably the most effective of all the bariatric procedures in terms of producing sustained weight loss over time. It does have potential long-term side effects and these include malabsorption, dumping, gallstone formation, stomal ulceration and hypoglycaemia. The mechanism of gallstone formation after bariatric surgery is multifactorial: rapid weight loss leads to increased cholesterol mobilisation from adipose tissue, resulting in supersaturation of bile with cholesterol. Additionally, reduced caloric intake decreases gallbladder stimulation and emptying, leading to bile stasis. The altered enterohepatic circulation of bile acids after gastric bypass surgery further contributes to lithogenic bile formation. On the positive side, diabetes becomes easier to manage and many of these patients will no longer require any medications for this condition. There may also be a reduction in risk for a number of cancers, including colorectal cancer - but the data for the reduction in risk for \u003Cstrong\u003Ecarcinoma of the prostate\u003C/strong\u003E is less clear.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst \u003Cstrong\u003Eregain in weight\u003C/strong\u003E is always a risk after bariatric surgery, only a very small proportion of patients who undergo Roux-en-Y gastric bypass surgery, regain their baseline weight.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPatients with pre-existing \u003Cstrong\u003Edepression\u003C/strong\u003E have a less predictable outcome after bariatric surgery as to whether there may be an improvement or worsening of their condition.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst sleeve gastrectomy may worsen \u003Cstrong\u003Egastro-oesophageal reflux disease\u003C/strong\u003E, this is not an issue after Roux-en-Y gastric bypass.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThus the most serious potential consequence that the patient should be counselled on is his risk (10-100 fold) of \u003Cstrong\u003Edeveloping gallstones\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Gallstone formation is very common after successful weight loss surgery."],"references":["Jakobsen GS, Smastuen MC, Sandbu R, et al. Association of Bariatric Surgery vs Medical Obesity Treatment With Long-term Medical Complications and Obesity-Related Comorbidies. JAMA 2018;319:291-301. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29340680/","Switzer NJ, Debru E, Church N, et al. The Impact of Bariatric Surgery on Depression: a Review. Currently Cardiovasc Risk Rep 2016;10:12. Available at: https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12170-016-0492-7","Wiggins T, Antonowicz SS, Markar SR. Cancer Risk Following Bariatric Surgery\u2014Systematic Review and Meta-analysis of National Population-Based Cohort Studies. Obesity Surgery 2019; 1031-39. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30591985/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93626"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2062"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93626","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/93626"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-08-16T09:33:55+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-16T09:35:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2062"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111539"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/76"}